Backport upstream fix: check root radius for NaN/Inf after fnewton in
the standard-FP path of mps_thread_fpolzer_worker.

Without this guard, when the standard floating-point Newton iteration
in mps_thread_fpolzer_worker produces a correction that is finite but
the associated root inclusion-radius (root[i]->frad) overflows to NaN
or Inf, MPSolve proceeds with that bad radius and SIGFPEs downstream.
The bug was deterministic at -j1 (single worker thread) and effectively
invisible at -j>=2 because the multi-block iteration order changed the
specific root index that hit the overflow.

Reported by Advanpix via the N=470 reproducer
(work/incoming/N470_bug.pol, work/incoming/MPSOLVE_BUG_REPORT.md).
Fixed upstream by Leonardo Robol on 2026-05-26 in commit 282b77c on
the master branch; will ship in MPSolve 3.2.3. Quote from the author:

  "Apparently, the dynamics of Newton's iteration is different
   (which makes sense, because the order is not deterministic and
   the roots are updated in blocks), and this somewhat avoided the
   problem with computing the radius for the root number 118, which
   was overflowing. Note that this is something that could happen,
   and a check was in place to switch to DPE arithmetic which has a
   longer exponent. Unfortunately, the check only looked at the
   approximation and not the radius. I have now changed this."

This patch is a strict subset of upstream 282b77c: it includes only
the src/libmps/monomial/monomial-threading.c hunk and omits the
configure.ac version bump (still labelled 3.2.2 in the tarball we
pin). Once we bump PSMM_MPSOLVE_COMMIT to 3.2.3, this patch can be
removed.

Upstream: https://github.com/robol/MPSolve/commit/282b77c25667257b20a0d4d680e82da61ffb49a1
Author: Leonardo Robol <leo@robol.it>

diff --git a/src/libmps/monomial/monomial-threading.c b/src/libmps/monomial/monomial-threading.c
index 590971d2..dc8af875 100644
--- a/src/libmps/monomial/monomial-threading.c
+++ b/src/libmps/monomial/monomial-threading.c
@@ -62,10 +62,11 @@ mps_thread_fpolzer_worker (void *data_ptr)
 
           mps_polynomial_fnewton (s, p, s->root[i], corr);
 
-	  if (cplx_check_fpe (corr))
+	  if (cplx_check_fpe (corr) || isnan(s->root[i]->frad) || isinf(s->root[i]->frad))
 	    {
 	      /* If we get a floating point exception we need to switch to DPE
 	       * arithmetic. */
+        MPS_DEBUG (s, "Floating point exception detected, switching to DPE arithmetic");
 	      s->root[i]->frad = rad1;
 	      s->skip_float = true;
 	      s->root[i]->again = false;
